The paper proposes a channel pruning technique for accelerating the computations of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image learning benchmarks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on optimization and training methods, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of stochastic training, which is relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image learning benchmarks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
